    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Ceremonial vessels used for holding fresh water during tea ceremonies. The water was used for washing the tea bowls and filling the kettle. Mizusashi are typically made of ceramic or lacquerware, but wooden and glass ones are also used.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
